@endnode

@node "usage" "AmiDog's Movie Player - Usage"

 -- Soon to come --
 
 Just doubleclick the file named AMP!

@endnode

@node "settings" "AmiDog's Movie Player - Settings"

 ColorModes:
 
  * Gray (8 bit)     - 256 colors, gray display.
  * Color (8 bit)    - 224 colors, ordered dithering.
  * Color (8 bit HQ) - 224 colors, ordered dithering, HighQuality (ONLY on 4:2:0 interlaced MPEGs).
  * Gray (4 bit)     - 16 colors, gray display.

@endnode

@node "speed" "AmiDog's Movie Player - Speed"

 Speed difference: (My measurement using a clock and a Wallace and Gromit MPEG, 240*176 pixels)
 
  * Color (8 bit) : 18 sek. -> 9 sek. using AGA mode (C2P), added 981203
  * Gray (8 bit)  : 17 sek.
  * Gray (4 bit)  : 11 sek.

 The total time it took to play the anim is what is shown. The major difference between the
 8 bit and 4 bit gray is due to the C2P taking a lot of time (it still runs on the 68k, since
 it's using WPA8, the difference is probably way smaller with a 060 companion CPU).

 More accurate figures will come in the near future!

 IMPORTANT: IsisPPC takes 18.3 secs to play the Wallace and Gromit MPEG which I've used above,
 this means that AMP is TWICE as fast as Isis on an AGA Amiga!!! And that is using a C-only C2P,
 not a single line of asm code has been used!

 All tests are performed using an A1200 603e'200, 040'25, 32MB and OS3.0.

@endnode

