@node "history" "AmiDog's Movie Player - History"

 v0.00  -981104
        -First working version! It's still 68k only, and uses WPA8 for displaying the graphics
         and as all of you know, that's SLOW! I'll compile a PPC version and ditch WPA8 ASAP.
        -981112
        -Well, what's happening, not much actually. I've not gotten GCC PPC to work yet, sadly.
         I've however spent a while examining the MPEG2 decoder source, and I think I know how
         to make it output 24bit data, or gray or whatever I like.
        -981124
        -I got GCC PPC working yesterday! Sadly it don't want to compile my MPEG-2 player, but
         I hope to get it fixed soon. I have however added GRAY output, so the 68k version
         has become a little bit faster.
        -A little later. I've now gotten the first version of my GUI to work, it wont send any
         settings to the MPEG2 player yet, but atleast I can now play MPEGs without using shell!
        -981127
        -Still no PPC version. The GUI is however fully functional now. I've been able to make
         a PPC compile which outputs the GFX to files, but it wont work with Amiga display yet.
        -981129
        -No PPC version yet... I've gotten a bit unsystemfriendly with the latest version. I've
         removed the "invisible window" which was used to catch mouseevents and added a simple
         register read instead, this solved some of my problems actually, however since it is
         only executed between the frames, you might have to hold down the left mouse button
         for a few 1/10 seconds before it'll exit. Oh, and I've added a 4 bit (16 color) gray
         mode as well.
        -A little later. Guess what!? Yes! The PPC version is up and running!!! And it's damn
         fast too!

 v0.10  -981129
        -First version with working PPC MPEG2 plugin!
        -981201
        -I had planned to release v0.10 but I'll probably wait until I've got a faster C2P
         than WPA8 as I'm currently using.

 v0.11  -981203
        -I've gotten the C2P up and running! It's a C-only one (no asm!) and it runs on the PPC.
         The speed is quite good, not to say quite excellent! It's TWICE as fast as IsisPPC on
         my AGA Amiga! IMPORTANT: This release is to be considered as a beta, it might contain
         a lot of bugs!

 v0.12  -981204
        -A couple of bugfixes and improvements, please check the homepage!

@endnode
